  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "It feels kind of weird to have on each item a field with the state of the other items. Something that feels a bit cleaner (but is probably too verbose) would be to provide a \"toggle\" function : \n\n``` js\nrefine(toggle(item.value))\ncreateURL(toggle(item.value))\n```\n\nThe main advantage of this API is that it's possible to implement \"clear\" buttons (`createURL({})`, `refine({})`). The \"business\" logic of how to toggle items would be contained in the `toggle` function. For multi-select, it's a classic toggle, while for Menu toggling an item unselects the previously selected item.\n",
    "created_at": "2016-09-19T21:41:40Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1305#issuecomment-248136054",
    "id": 248136054,
